I had a mailer coupon for their opening to take 50% off our meal, so the kids and I stopped in for lunch yesterday.
We ordered a lot of food, BLT and Caesar salad for the kids, chop salad and red pepper lobster soup for me, chocolate creme brulee for the kids, it also came with bread and chocolate covered strawberries.
With the coupon, we were still under $10!
That was way cool!
If I were to consider paying full price for a latter visit the portions were small.
I was really impressed with some of the food (Caesar was freaking amazing, and the soup was surprisingly realllllly good) but disappointed with others (chop was meh, the ingredients weren't fresh enough).
I will come back for a chicken Caesar for sure!
and to try other stuff, the sandwiches looked awesome!
